s\nfrom classes. This is used to show that $\\mathrm{BAC}^+$, a subsystem of\n$\\mathrm{NBG}$, decides every $2$-sentence in the language of class theory that\nincludes a unary predicate distinguishing sets from classes.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 14 Dec 2020 05:44:19 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 23 Feb 2021 08:39:02 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 18 Apr 2022 14:05:56 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Sun, 11 Sep 2022 15:12:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-09-13"}
